Package org.framework.rodolfo.freire.git.vertlog.service

Class BuyService

java.lang.Object
org.framework.rodolfo.freire.git.vertlog.service.BuyService
All Implemented Interfaces:
GenericsInterfaceService<Buy>
@Service public class BuyService extends Object implements GenericsInterfaceService<Buy>
Service layer class responsible for managing `Buy` entities.

This class implements the `GenericsInterfaceService` interface to provide basic CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations for `Buy` entities. It interacts with the `BuyRepository` to access and manipulate buy data in the underlying data source (e.g., database).

    • findBetweenDate

      public List<Buy> findBetweenDate(Date ini, Date end)
      Finds buy orders within a specified date range (not implemented yet).

      This method is intended to retrieve buy orders whose dates fall between the provided `ini` and `end` dates (inclusive). However, the current implementation returns an empty `Optional`. You should replace this with your logic to query the repository based on dates.

      Parameters:
      ini - The start date of the search range.
      end - The end date of the search range.
      Returns:
      An `Optional` object containing a list of `Buy` objects found within the date range (to be implemented).
